definition.value: An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the tertiary amino group of tiagabine.
A hydrochloride resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of tiagabine and hydrogen chloride. A GABA reuptake inhibitor, it is used for the treatment of epilepsy.

A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of five adenosine, seven guanosine, five uridine and eight cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-A-G-U-C-U-C-C-A-C-U-C-G-A-G-U-G-U-C-C-G-A-G-C-G.

A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of eight adenosine, seven guanosine, three uridine and seven cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-A-G-U-C-U-C-C-A-C-U-C-G-A-G-U-G-U-C-C-G-A-G-C-G.
A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of one uridine, one cytidine, four adenosine and four guanosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence U-G-G-G-A-A-G-A-C-A.
A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of four uridine, four adenosine and two guanosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-U-G-U-A-G-A-U-U-A.
A synthetic RNA fragment comprised of five adenosine, one guanosine, four uridine and three cytidine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence U-G-G-G-A-A-G-A-C-A.
An amino trisaccharide consisting of three N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2) and (1->3).
An amino trisaccharide consisting of three N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3) and (1->2).
An amino tetrasaccharide consisting of four N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->3) and (1->2).
An amino pentasaccharide consisting of five N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->3), (1->2) and (1->2).
An amino nonasaccharide consisting of nine N-formyl-alpha-D-perosamine residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->2), (1->2), (1->3), (1->2), (1->2), (1->2) and (1->2).
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerophosphoserine in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear chain of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, linked (1->3), (1->3) and (1->4) respectively, with an alpha-L-fucose residue linked to the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerophosphoserine in which the acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).
A triply charged acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-dehydrocarnityl CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A triply charged acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of N,N,N-trimethylglycyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino trisaccharide comprised of a linear sequence of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-galactosamine linked (1->4) and (1->6).
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol in which the acyl group is specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as heptadecanoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoglycerol in which the acyl group is specified as oleoyl.
A glycerophosphoglycerol where both glycerol moieties are attached at primary positions and one stereocentre has R-configuration.
A member of the family of mitomycins that exhibits antibiotic and antitumour properties as well as a high level of toxicity.
An iminium betaine resulting from a transfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the imino group of 5-hydroxyectoine.  It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A pteroate that is the conjugate base of (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropteroic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (Z)-hex-3-enoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the family of mitomycins that exhibits antibiotic and antitumour properties.

A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dTDP-beta-L-daunosamine, arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate group and protonation of the amino group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A member of the family of mitomycins that is mitomycin B in which the methoxy group  on the quinone ring is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A member of the family of mitomycins that is mitomycin A in which the methoxy group on the quinone ring is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of N-isopropyl-L-glutamine; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of N-(gamma-L-glutamyl)-L-alaninol; major species at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (S)-2-aminopropan-1-ol. The major species at pH 7.3 according to Marvin ver. 6.2.0.
Any glycine transporter inhibitor that interferes with the action of glycine 2 transporters.
Any substance that inhibits the action of glycine transporters.
A nitrile that is propionitrile in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a phenyl group.
A triglyceride in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as palmitoyl while that at position 3 is specified as palmitoleoyl.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from trans-3-hydroxy-L-proline.
A glycerophospholipid that is the monoethyl ester of any phosphatidic acid.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the 5-hydroxy to the tertiary amino group of 11-deoxy-beta-rhodomycin; major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylethanol in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl).
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is GDP substituted at position 2' by an N-methylanthraniloyl group.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of glutamine hydroxamate; major species at pH 7.3.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate that is GDP substituted at the 3' position by an N-methylanthraniloyl group.
An 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoserine in which the 1-acyl group is specified as arachidonoyl.
A glucotetrose consisting of alpha-maltotriose with a further alpha-D-glucose unit linked to O-6 of the glucose residue at the non-reducing end.
A heptasaccharide consisting of two alpha-maltotriose units linked (1->6), with a further alpha-D-glucose unit linked to O-6 of the glucose residue at the non-reducing end.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine that is L-carnitine having decenoyl group as the acyl substituent in which the position of the double bond is unspecified.
